						<summary>

						<p>On a tablet fixed on a dilapitated tomb near the church in the village.</p>						

						<p>1790 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Christian year 1790 A.D., Sādharaṇa, Āśvija, śu. 12, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It records the death of Inayya (a Christian convert), son of Niḍamāmiḷḷa Rājappa and Akkamma, an employee (prānsu pādushā) under the French Government at Pudicheri-paṭṭana i.e., present Puducheri of Tamil Nadu. A French version of the record is engraved below the above Telugu varsion.</p>						

						</summary>
